==English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /ˌklæɹɪˈnɛt/ or /ˌklɛɹɪˈnɛt/

===Etymology===
Learned borrowing from Italian ''clarinetto'', diminutive of ''clarino'' meaning "[[trumpet]]" (as the first clarinets had a strident tone similar to that of a trumpet)

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# a [[woodwind]] [[musical instrument]] that has a distinctive liquid [[tone]] whose characteristics vary among its three registers: [[chalumeau]] (low), [[clarion]] (medium), and [[altissimo]] (high).

